page.title: 19BANCHORY-DEVENICK WILDLIFE 2
page.content: The{woods and forests}are made up of {coniferous and deciduous}trees. Since the 1930's there has been quite a lot of tree planting as the value of the timber has risen. Banchory-Devenick is some{600 feet above sea level and there is nearly always a{wind.}In summer the{haar reaches here and blocks out the warm sunshine. In winter there can be{snow {and ice}up in this area and yet mild weather in Aberdeen. In winter we hear the{Arctic geese migrating south and then north again in the spring. In summer the{swifts and{swallows}may visit but in small numbers.
